      A broadcast record is one which contains all of the specific parameters
      which are customized and exclusive for a specific relay application.
      The X2X system is configured to handle up to 16 relay applications,
      where a relay application is one which is used to relay information
      to a list of defined stations or terminals (ie. downloads, odds
      updates, etc).
 
      Adding A Relay Application
      ==========================
      To add a relay broadcast record to the Distributed Network,
      enter "1" (for Add Application), and press return.  The program will
      then prompt for the application number. If the application already
      exists, an error message will be displayed, and you will be prompted
      for relay application information.
 
 
 
 
 
